(43, 6, 24, 43, 6, 17, 17, 'Capernaum', 'Journey to Capernaum', 'Both passages emphasize the journey to Capernaum, where Jesus is sought after. The mention of entering a ship in darkness in John 6:17 connects to the people''s search for Jesus in John 6:24.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 24, 41, 1, 37, 37, 'seeking for Jesus', 'Seeking Jesus Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of people actively seeking Jesus. In John 6:24, the crowd is described as seeking for Jesus, while in Mark 1:37, the disciples report that all men seek for him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 24, 41, 6, 53, 53, 'seeking for Jesus', 'Journey to Find Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the movement of people seeking Jesus. In John, the people take shipping to find Him, while in Mark, they arrive at the shore after crossing over. This connection highlights the theme of pursuit in the narratives.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 24, 42, 8, 40, 40, 'seeking for Jesus', 'Seeking and Receiving Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the people''s desire for Jesus. In John, they are ''seeking for Jesus,'' while in Luke, they ''gladly received him.'' This connection highlights the anticipation and eagerness of the people towards Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 24, 40, 14, 34, 34, 'seeking for Jesus', 'Journey to Find Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the movement of people seeking Jesus. In John 6:24, the people actively seek Jesus in Capernaum, while in Matthew 14:34, they arrive in Gennesaret, indicating a continued pursuit of Him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 24, 43, 6, 23, 23, 'seeking for Jesus', 'Connection of Seeking Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the people''s search for Jesus after the miraculous feeding. The mention of boats in John 6:23 indicates the means by which they sought Him, linking directly to their actions in John 6:24.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 25, 43, 1, 38, 39, NULL, 'Inquiry about Jesus'' Location', 'Both passages emphasize a question posed to Jesus regarding his whereabouts. In John 6:25, the crowd asks, ''when camest thou hither?'' while in John 1:38, the disciples inquire, ''where dwellest thou?'' This connection highlights the curiosity of those seeking Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 25, 40, 23, 7, 7, 'Rabbi', 'Connection of the term ''Rabbi''', 'This connection highlights the use of the term ''Rabbi'' in both passages, emphasizing the recognition of authority and teaching. In John 6:25, the people address Jesus as ''Rabbi,'' while in Matthew 23:7, the term is noted as a title of respect in social contexts.', 'keyword', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 26, 59, 4, 3, 4, 'ye did eat of the loaves', 'Desire and Spiritual Fulfillment', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking fulfillment. In John 6:26, the crowd seeks Jesus for physical satisfaction, while James 4:3-4 warns against asking for selfish desires. Both passages emphasize the importance of the motives behind one''s desires.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 26, 50, 3, 19, 19, 'did eat of the loaves', 'Connection of Earthly Desires', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking fulfillment in earthly things. Both passages emphasize the danger of prioritizing physical satisfaction, as seen in ''God is their belly'' and ''did eat of the loaves.''', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 26, 50, 2, 21, 21, 'Ye seek me, not because', 'Self-Interest in Seeking Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of self-interest in both passages. John 6:26 points out that the crowd sought Jesus for their own satisfaction, while Philippians 2:21 notes that many seek their own interests rather than those of Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 26, 26, 33, 31, 31, 'because ye did eat of the loaves', 'Seeking for Fulfillment', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking fulfillment for selfish desires. Both passages emphasize the superficiality of following for personal gain, as seen in the people''s hunger in John and their covetousness in Ezekiel.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 26, 44, 8, 18, 21, 'ye seek me, not because ye saw', 'Motivation for Seeking Power', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking Jesus and spiritual gifts for selfish reasons. In both passages, individuals are motivated by personal gain rather than genuine faith or understanding.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 26, 54, 6, 5, 5, 'ye did eat of the loaves', 'Seeking Gain vs. True Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking Jesus for material gain rather than spiritual truth. Both passages emphasize the dangers of corrupt motives in faith, contrasting genuine belief with the pursuit of earthly benefits.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 26, 45, 16, 18, 18, NULL, 'Connection of Self-Serving Motives', 'This connection highlights the theme of serving one''s own desires. Both passages emphasize the idea of individuals seeking fulfillment for their own benefit rather than genuine devotion.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 27, 51, 3, 2, 2, 'meat which endureth unto everlasting life', 'Focus on Eternal vs. Earthly', 'This connection highlights the contrast between seeking temporary sustenance and prioritizing eternal life. Both passages emphasize the importance of valuing spiritual matters over earthly concerns.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 27, 23, 55, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of Spiritual Sustenance', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of seeking temporary satisfaction and encourage the pursuit of lasting nourishment for the soul. They highlight the importance of seeking what truly satisfies and endures, rather than what is fleeting.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 27, 43, 6, 54, 54, 'meat which endureth unto everlasting life', 'Eternal Life and Spiritual Nourishment', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of eternal life. The first passage speaks of ''meat which endureth unto everlasting life,'' while the second directly connects eating Christ''s flesh and drinking His blood to having eternal life.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 27, 55, 2, 19, 19, 'for him hath God the Father sealed', 'Enduring Meat and God''s Seal', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a seal from God, indicating divine recognition and assurance. John 6:27 speaks of the Son of man being sealed by God, while 2 Timothy 2:19 mentions the foundation of God having a seal that identifies His own.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 27, 40, 6, 19, 19, 'meat which endureth unto everlasting life', 'Eternal vs. Earthly Treasures', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking what endures rather than what perishes. John 6:27 speaks of ''meat which endureth unto everlasting life,'' while Matthew 6:19 warns against ''treasures upon earth'' that are corruptible.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 27, 43, 6, 40, 40, 'everlasting life', 'Connection of Everlasting Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of everlasting life, with John 6:27 urging believers to seek the enduring ''meat'' that leads to it, while John 6:40 explicitly states that belief in the Son results in everlasting life. This connection highlights the importance of faith in Jesus for eternal sustenance.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 27, 45, 6, 23, 23, 'meat which endureth unto everlasting life', 'Eternal Life Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of eternal life. John 6:27 speaks of ''meat which endureth unto everlasting life,'' while Romans 6:23 contrasts death with ''the gift of God is eternal life.''', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 28, 44, 16, 30, 30, NULL, 'Questions of Faith and Action', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking guidance on how to act in relation to faith. Both passages emphasize a question about what one must do, linking the concept of works in John to the necessity of salvation in Acts.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 28, 40, 19, 16, 16, 'what shall we do', 'Seeking Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the question of what actions are necessary to attain a desired spiritual outcome. In John, the focus is on ''the works of God,'' while in Matthew, the inquiry is about ''good thing'' for eternal life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 28, 42, 10, 25, 25, 'What shall we do', 'Seeking Guidance for Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize a quest for understanding how to achieve a significant spiritual goal. In John 6:28, the question is about working the works of God, while in Luke 10:25, the inquiry is about inheriting eternal life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 28, 44, 9, 6, 6, 'what shall we do', 'Call to Action in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize a quest for guidance on what actions to take in service to God. The question in John 6:28 about ''what shall we do'' parallels the inquiry in Acts 9:6, where the speaker asks, ''what wilt thou have me to do?''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 28, 5, 5, 27, 27, 'work the works of God', 'Works of God and Obedience', 'This connection highlights the theme of doing God''s will. Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing and acting upon God''s words, as seen in the desire to ''work the works of God'' and the commitment to ''hear it, and do it.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 28, 33, 6, 7, 8, 'that we might work the works of God', 'Works of God and Justice', 'This connection highlights the inquiry into what constitutes the ''works of God'' in John 6:28 and the explicit requirements of God in Micah 6:8. Both passages emphasize the importance of ethical living, including justice and mercy, as central to fulfilling divine expectations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 28, 24, 42, 3, 6, 'that we might work the works of God', 'Seeking Guidance from God', 'Both passages emphasize a desire to know what actions to take in accordance with God''s will. In John 6:28, the question is posed about working the works of God, while Jeremiah 42:3 expresses a plea for direction on how to walk and act. This connection highlights a common theme of seeking divine guidance.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 29, 62, 3, 23, 23, 'believe on him whom he hath sent', 'Connection of Belief in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in Jesus Christ. John 6:29 highlights belief as the work of God, while 1 John 3:23 reiterates it as a commandment to believe in the Son.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
